; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures SCU PWR and reads/writes backup data.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Supply power to external power port by a suitable instrument or make a environment to generate low voltage under 1.6V.
;    Measure PC13 port whether proper frequency is available or not.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. SCUPWR
;    2. SCULVD
;    3. RTC
;    4. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. RTC0   : PC13 (RTC Clock Output)
;
; E. Note
;    RTC module should be enabled.
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; SCUPWR
; 1. BAKDW                       : [ 0 0xffff0000 1 0xaaaa5555 2 0x5555aaaa 3 0x0000ffff ]
;    Backup Data Index           : 0 / 1 / 2 / 3
;    Backup Data                 : 0xffff0000 / 0xaaaa5555 / 0x5555aaaa / 0x0000ffff
;
; 2. BAKDR                       : [ 0 1 2 3 ]
;    Backup Data Index           : 0 / 1 / 2 / 3
;
; 3. BAK                         : [ e ]
;    Backup Mode                 : e (enable)
;
; RTC0
; 1. Channel                     : 0 (RTC 0)
;
; 2. Clock                       : [ 0 l ]
;    Source                      : l (LSI40KHz)
;
; 3. Config                      : [ 0 i -meas ]
;    Operation                   : i (Interrupt)
;    Measuring fRTC at PC13 port : N/A
;
; PCU (PC13)
; 1. Port Group                : 2 (PCU Port C)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 1 13 a 7 ]
;    Pin Number                : 13
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 7 (RTC_TAMP1)
;
; PCU (PC13)
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 1 13 a 7'
mpause 30

; RTC0
sendln 'cm rtc'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'clk 0 l'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 i -meas'
mpause 30
sendln 'start 0'
mpause 30

; SCULVD
sendln 'cm sculvd'
mpause 30
sendln 'lvr d'
mpause 30

; SCUPWR
sendln 'cm scupwr'
mpause 30
sendln 'bakdr 0 1 2 3'
mpause 40
sendln 'bakdw 0 0x0 1 0x0 2 0x0 3 0x0'
mpause 30
sendln 'bakdr 0 1 2 3'
mpause 40
sendln 'bakdw 0 0xffff0000 1 0xaaaa5555 2 0x5555aaaa 3 0x0000ffff'
mpause 30
sendln 'bakdr 0 1 2 3'
mpause 40
sendln 'bak e'
